name: Downward Dog
desc: This famous pose works to strengthen the core and improve circulation. A deep hamstring stretch spreads to the eintire body aiding in flexibility. To perform this pose, start in a plank with your hands slightly lower than normal. Extend and lengthen your spine, simultaneously pressing through the palms of your hands and balls of your feet. Pull your pelvis up toward the ceiling, using the triceps in your upper arms to help stabilize your form. Hold this position and breathe deeply for the duration of the exercise.
